    <text id="B0243T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Stitt asks about the Registers (of Marriages?) in Staunton</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Thomas P. Jackson<lb/>Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        
                        <name type="place">Winchester <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have learned from <abbr expan="Captain">Capt.</abbr>
                    <orig reg="McDonnell">McDonal</orig> that the Registers <orig reg="were"
                    >ware</orig> not appointed in Staunton Mr. Stitt &amp; I are from the State
                    of <orig reg="Pennsylvania">Pensyvania</orig> we are living in Winchester at
                    present we have <orig reg="both">boath</orig> been in <abbr expan="Pennsylvania"
                        >Pa.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="recently">Recty</abbr> &amp; if they are not appointed please
                    let us know &amp; by you doing so you will <orig reg="oblige">oblidge</orig>
                    us by doing so.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute><orig reg="Addressed">Adres</orig> with kindest wished</salute>
                    <signed>William Stitt</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
